<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11069l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11069l">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11069l"> 69(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &agrave; perp&egrave;te / , cipal / garde municipal</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Je veux dire que le g&eacute;nie du fran&ccedil;ais, qui s&apos;oppose aux mots trops longs, s&apos;exerce encore, malgr&eacute; tous les obstacles que lui dressent la p&eacute;danterie et la pr&eacute;tention, sur les vocables dont on nous assassine: <i>photographie</i> devient rapidement <i>photo;</i> <i>m&eacute;tropolitain</i>, <i>m&eacute;tro;</i> <i>automobile</i>, <i>auto;</i> <i>cin&eacute;matographie</i>, <i>cin&eacute;;</i> <i>v&eacute;locip&egrave;de</i>, <i>v&eacute;lo;</i> <i>pneumatique</i>, <i>pneu;</i> <i>taxim&egrave;tre</i>, <i>taxi; </i>voire <mark><i>garde municipal</i>, <i>cipal</i>, et <i>&agrave; perp&eacute;tuit&eacute;</i>, <i>&agrave; perp&egrave;te</i></mark>. <font color="green">[I want to say that the genius of the French language, which does not like words that are too long, still resists, despite the obstacles thrown in its path by pedantry and pretention, those words with which we are attacked: <i>photographie</i> quickly becomes <i>photo</i>; <i>m&eacute;tropolitain</i>, <i>metro</i>; <i>automobile, auto; cin&eacute;matographie, cin&eacute;; velocipede, v&eacute;lo; pneumatique, pneu; taximeter, taxi; </i>see also <i>garde municipal, cipal, </i>and <i>&agrave; perp&eacute;tuit&eacute;</i>, <i>&agrave; perp&egrave;te</i>;]</font> <small> Jacques Boulenger et Andr&eacute; Th&eacute;rive, <a name="JBAT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JBAT"><cite title="source">Les Soir&eacute;es du Grammaire-Club</cite></a> (1924) 94</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
